<% title = "Stress Management | Women's Health Hub" %>

<div class="container py-5">
  <div class="row">
    <div class="col-lg-8">
      <h1 class="mb-4">Stress Management for Women</h1>
      <p class="lead mb-4">
        Chronic stress can negatively impact both physical and mental health.
        Learn effective techniques to manage stress and enhance your overall
        well-being.
      </p>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Understanding Stress</h5>

          <p>
            Stress is your body's natural response to pressure from challenging
            or demanding situations. While short-term stress can be motivating,
            chronic stress can lead to serious health issues, including:
          </p>

          <div class="row mb-4">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <ul>
                <li>Disrupted sleep patterns</li>
                <li>Irregular menstrual cycles</li>
                <li>Digestive problems</li>
                <li>Decreased immunity</li>
                <li>Headaches and muscle tension</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <ul>
                <li>Anxiety and depression</li>
                <li>Difficulty concentrating</li>
                <li>Weight changes</li>
                <li>Increased blood pressure</li>
                <li>Heightened inflammation</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <p>
            Women often experience unique stressors related to multiple roles in
            family and work life, hormonal changes, societal expectations, and
            systemic inequalities. Recognizing your stress triggers is the first
            step toward managing them effectively.
          </p>

          <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-lightbulb me-2"></i>
            <strong>Did you know?</strong> Stress affects women and men
            differently due to hormonal variations. Women are more likely to
            report physical and emotional symptoms of stress than men.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Effective Stress Management Techniques</h5>

          <div class="accordion" id="stressAccordion">
            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingOne">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseOne"
                  aria-expanded="true"
                  aria-controls="collapseOne"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-lungs me-2 text-primary"></i> Breathwork &
                  Meditation
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseOne"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse show"
                aria-labelledby="headingOne"
                data-bs-parent="#stressAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <p>
                        Controlled breathing activates your parasympathetic
                        nervous system, which helps counteract the stress
                        response.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Try this: 4-7-8 Breathing</h6>
                      <ol>
                        <li>Inhale quietly through your nose for 4 seconds</li>
                        <li>Hold your breath for 7 seconds</li>
                        <li>
                          Exhale completely through your mouth for 8 seconds
                        </li>
                        <li>Repeat 3-4 times</li>
                      </ol>

                      <p>
                        Regular meditation practice has been shown to reduce
                        stress, anxiety, and cortisol levels. Even just 5-10
                        minutes daily can make a difference.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
                      <i
                        class="fas fa-om fa-5x text-primary opacity-75 mb-3"
                      ></i>
                      <p class="small text-muted">
                        Meditation can be practiced anywhere, anytime.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingTwo">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseTwo"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseTwo"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-walking me-2 text-primary"></i> Physical
                  Activity
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseTwo"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingTwo"
                data-bs-parent="#stressAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-8">
                      <p>
                        Exercise releases endorphins, which are natural mood
                        elevators. It also decreases stress hormones like
                        cortisol over time.
                      </p>

                      <h6 class="mt-3">Stress-Reducing Activities:</h6>
                      <ul>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Yoga:</strong> Combines physical movement with
                          breathwork and mindfulness
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Walking:</strong> Accessible, low-impact way
                          to get moving and clear your mind
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Dancing:</strong> Expressive movement that
                          releases tension and boosts mood
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Tai Chi:</strong> Gentle flowing movements
                          that promote relaxation
                        </li>
                        <li>
                          <strong>Swimming:</strong> Water-based exercise that
                          reduces physical tension
                        </li>
                      </ul>

                      <p>
                        Aim for at least 30 minutes of moderate activity most
                        days of the week. Remember, it's about consistency, not
                        intensity.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-4 text-center">
                      <i
                        class="fas fa-heartbeat fa-5x text-primary opacity-75 mb-3"
                      ></i>
                      <p class="small text-muted">
                        Find activities you enjoy to make movement a pleasure,
                        not a chore.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingThree">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseThree"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseThree"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-brain me-2 text-primary"></i> Cognitive
                  Techniques
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseThree"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingThree"
                data-bs-parent="#stressAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    How you think about stressful situations can greatly
                    influence how they affect you. Cognitive techniques help
                    reshape negative thought patterns.
                  </p>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Useful Strategies:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Thought reframing:</strong> Challenge negative
                      thoughts by asking "Is this thought helpful?" or "What's a
                      more balanced perspective?"
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Gratitude practice:</strong> Regularly noting
                      things you're thankful for can shift focus from stressors
                      to positive aspects of life
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Mindfulness:</strong> Paying attention to the
                      present moment without judgment helps reduce rumination
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      <strong>Self-compassion:</strong> Treating yourself with
                      the same kindness you would offer a good friend
                    </li>
                  </ul>

                  <div class="alert alert-success">
                    <strong>Try this:</strong> When facing a stressful
                    situation, ask yourself "Will this matter in five years?" to
                    gain perspective.
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFour">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseFour"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseFour"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-users me-2 text-primary"></i> Social
                  Connection
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseFour"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingFour"
                data-bs-parent="#stressAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Social support is a powerful buffer against stress. Women
                    who maintain strong social connections tend to manage stress
                    more effectively and enjoy better health outcomes.
                  </p>

                  <h6 class="mt-3">Ways to Nurture Connections:</h6>
                  <ul>
                    <li>Schedule regular check-ins with friends and family</li>
                    <li>Join community groups aligned with your interests</li>
                    <li>
                      Consider support groups if facing specific challenges
                    </li>
                    <li>Volunteer for causes you care about</li>
                    <li>Practice active listening in your relationships</li>
                  </ul>

                  <p>
                    <strong>Remember:</strong> Quality matters more than
                    quantity. A few deep, meaningful relationships can provide
                    more support than many superficial connections.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="accordion-item">
              <h2 class="accordion-header" id="headingFive">
                <button
                  class="accordion-button collapsed"
                  type="button"
                  data-bs-toggle="collapse"
                  data-bs-target="#collapseFive"
                  aria-expanded="false"
                  aria-controls="collapseFive"
                >
                  <i class="fas fa-leaf me-2 text-primary"></i> Lifestyle
                  Factors
                </button>
              </h2>
              <div
                id="collapseFive"
                class="accordion-collapse collapse"
                aria-labelledby="headingFive"
                data-bs-parent="#stressAccordion"
              >
                <div class="accordion-body">
                  <p>
                    Your daily habits and routines can either contribute to or
                    help alleviate stress.
                  </p>

                  <div class="row">
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <h6>Sleep</h6>
                      <p>
                        Quality sleep is essential for stress management. Aim
                        for 7-9 hours of sleep per night and establish a
                        consistent sleep schedule.
                      </p>

                      <h6>Nutrition</h6>
                      <p>
                        A balanced diet supports your body's stress response.
                        Limit caffeine, alcohol, and highly processed foods,
                        which can exacerbate stress.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md-6">
                      <h6>Time in Nature</h6>
                      <p>
                        Spending time outdoors has been shown to lower stress
                        hormones. Try to incorporate "green time" into your
                        weekly routine.
                      </p>

                      <h6>Boundaries</h6>
                      <p>
                        Learning to say no and setting healthy boundaries in
                        work and personal relationships is crucial for managing
                        stress levels.
                      </p>
                    </div>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Hormones and Stress</h5>

          <p>
            Women's hormonal fluctuations throughout the month and across
            different life stages can influence stress responses.
          </p>

          <div class="table-responsive">
            <table class="table">
              <thead>
                <tr>
                  <th>Life Stage</th>
                  <th>Hormonal Factors</th>
                  <th>Stress Management Considerations</th>
                </tr>
              </thead>
              <tbody>
                <tr>
                  <td>Menstrual Cycle</td>
                  <td>Fluctuations in estrogen and progesterone</td>
                  <td>
                    Stress management needs may vary depending on cycle phase;
                    track symptoms to identify patterns
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Pregnancy</td>
                  <td>Dramatic increases in hormones</td>
                  <td>
                    Gentle exercise, adequate rest, and pregnancy-safe
                    relaxation techniques are important
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Postpartum</td>
                  <td>Rapid hormone shifts after delivery</td>
                  <td>
                    Social support is crucial; professional help may be needed
                    for postpartum mood disorders
                  </td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                  <td>Perimenopause/Menopause</td>
                  <td>Declining estrogen and fluctuating hormones</td>
                  <td>
                    Stress reduction becomes especially important;
                    hormone-balancing lifestyle practices can help
                  </td>
                </tr>
              </tbody>
            </table>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3">
            <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i> Tracking your stress levels
            alongside your menstrual cycle can help you identify patterns and
            prepare for times when you might need extra self-care.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">When to Seek Help</h5>

          <p>
            While self-management techniques work well for everyday stress,
            sometimes professional support is needed. Consider reaching out if:
          </p>

          <ul>
            <li>
              You feel overwhelmed by stress despite trying self-help strategies
            </li>
            <li>
              Stress is interfering with your daily functioning or relationships
            </li>
            <li>You're experiencing symptoms of depression or anxiety</li>
            <li>You're using alcohol, drugs, or unhealthy behaviors to cope</li>
            <li>You have thoughts of harming yourself</li>
          </ul>

          <p>Options for professional support include:</p>
          <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <ul>
                <li>Primary care physician</li>
                <li>Mental health therapist or counselor</li>
                <li>Psychiatrist</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-6">
              <ul>
                <li>Support groups</li>
                <li>Employee assistance programs</li>
                <li>Crisis hotlines</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="alert alert-warning">
            <i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle me-2"></i>
            <strong>Remember:</strong> Seeking help is a sign of strength, not
            weakness. Many effective treatments exist for stress-related
            conditions.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="col-lg-4 mt-4 mt-lg-0">
      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Quick Stress Relief Techniques</h5>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-hand-sparkles fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">5-4-3-2-1 Grounding</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Name 5 things you see, 4 things you feel, 3 things you hear, 2
                things you smell, and 1 thing you taste.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-spa fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Progressive Muscle Relaxation</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Tense and then release each muscle group, starting from your
                toes and working up to your head.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-cloud-rain fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Visualization</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Close your eyes and imagine a peaceful place, engaging all your
                senses.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center mb-3">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-music fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Music Therapy</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Listen to calming music for just 5 minutes to reduce stress
                hormones.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="d-flex align-items-center">
            <div class="flex-shrink-0 me-3">
              <div
                class="bg-primary text-white rounded-circle d-flex align-items-center justify-content-center"
                style="width: 50px; height: 50px"
              >
                <i class="fas fa-pen fa-lg"></i>
              </div>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h6 class="mb-0">Expressive Writing</h6>
              <p class="small mb-0">
                Spend 10 minutes writing about your feelings to process and
                release them.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card mb-4">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Stress Journal</h5>
          <p>
            Track your stress levels and identify patterns to better manage your
            response.
          </p>

          <form>
            <div class="mb-3">
              <label for="stress-date" class="form-label">Date</label>
              <input type="date" class="form-control" id="stress-date" />
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <label class="form-label">Stress Level (1-10)</label>
              <div class="range">
                <input
                  type="range"
                  class="form-range"
                  min="1"
                  max="10"
                  step="1"
                  id="stress-level"
                />
                <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
                  <span>1</span>
                  <span>5</span>
                  <span>10</span>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <label for="stress-triggers" class="form-label">Triggers</label>
              <textarea
                class="form-control"
                id="stress-triggers"
                rows="2"
                placeholder="What caused your stress today?"
              ></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <label for="stress-symptoms" class="form-label">Symptoms</label>
              <textarea
                class="form-control"
                id="stress-symptoms"
                rows="2"
                placeholder="How did stress manifest in your body and mind?"
              ></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="mb-3">
              <label for="coping-strategies" class="form-label"
                >Coping Strategies Used</label
              >
              <textarea
                class="form-control"
                id="coping-strategies"
                rows="2"
                placeholder="What helped you manage your stress?"
              ></textarea>
            </div>

            <div class="d-grid">
              <button type="button" class="btn btn-primary">
                <i class="fas fa-save me-2"></i> Save Entry
              </button>
            </div>
          </form>

          <div class="alert alert-info mt-3 small">
            <i class="fas fa-info-circle me-2"></i> This is a demo feature. In
            the future, you'll be able to save and track your stress patterns
            over time.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="card">
        <div class="card-body">
          <h5 class="card-title">Helpful Resources</h5>
          <ul class="list-group list-group-flush">
            <li class="list-group-item">
              <a href="#" target="_blank"
                >National Institute of Mental Health</a
              >
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              <a href="#" target="_blank">American Psychological Association</a>
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              <a href="#" target="_blank">Office on Women's Health</a>
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              <a href="#" target="_blank"
                >Anxiety and Depression Association of America</a
              >
            </li>
            <li class="list-group-item">
              <a href="#" target="_blank">Mental Health America</a>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<script>
  document.addEventListener("DOMContentLoaded", function () {
    // Set today's date in the stress journal
    const today = new Date();
    const year = today.getFullYear();
    const month = String(today.getMonth() + 1).padStart(2, "0");
    const day = String(today.getDate()).padStart(2, "0");
    const formattedDate = `${year}-${month}-${day}`;
    const dateInput = document.getElementById("stress-date");
    if (dateInput) {
      dateInput.value = formattedDate;
    }
  });
</script>
